00:03:14.161 --> 00:03:19.800 align:middle line:84%
heart-centered life, but
what are some of the,

00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:22.903 align:middle line:84%
on the scientific part,
what are some of the,

00:03:22.903 --> 00:03:25.973 align:middle line:84%
because we hear a lot of the
coherence of the heart, huh?

00:03:25.973 --> 00:03:26.807 align:middle line:90%
This is a big one.

00:03:26.807 --> 00:03:28.142 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: It's a term, yeah.

00:03:28.142 --> 00:03:29.610 align:middle line:84%
Well, what we found was, and
it wasn't just our research.

00:03:29.610 --> 00:03:30.878 align:middle line:90%
This is what was interesting is

00:03:30.878 --> 00:03:32.279 align:middle line:84%
that the research
was scattered all

00:03:32.279 --> 00:03:33.380 align:middle line:90%
through the research literature.

00:03:33.380 --> 00:03:34.682 align:middle line:90%
You know, the story was there,

00:03:34.682 --> 00:03:37.785 align:middle line:84%
but nobody had connected the
dots and put it together.

00:03:37.785 --> 00:03:39.687 align:middle line:84%
And, what we found
was that the heart

00:03:39.687 --> 00:03:44.591 align:middle line:84%
at a physical level communicated
to us in four different ways.

00:03:44.591 --> 00:03:46.760 align:middle line:84%
There was a neurological
communication.

00:03:46.760 --> 00:03:47.895 align:middle line:90%
This was interesting.

00:03:47.895 --> 00:03:50.230 align:middle line:84%
There's a whole field
called neurocardiology.

00:03:50.230 --> 00:03:53.300 align:middle line:84%
Who knew? Studying this
very complex nervous system

00:03:53.300 --> 00:03:55.202 align:middle line:84%
that we have in the
physical heart.

00:03:55.202 --> 00:03:57.671 align:middle line:84%
Next to the brain is
the most complex part

00:03:57.671 --> 00:03:59.038 align:middle line:84%
of our nervous system
that we have,

00:03:59.038 --> 00:04:01.308 align:middle line:84%
and that little nervous
system communicates

00:04:01.308 --> 00:04:03.310 align:middle line:84%
with the big brain here
through a nerve pathway

00:04:03.310 --> 00:04:04.878 align:middle line:90%
that starts out in our heart.

00:04:04.878 --> 00:04:07.114 align:middle line:84%
It goes up, it comes
in through the brain,

00:04:07.114 --> 00:04:09.016 align:middle line:84%
all the way through the
lower brain centers,

00:04:09.016 --> 00:04:10.384 align:middle line:84%
in through the midbrain,
where a lot

00:04:10.384 --> 00:04:12.019 align:middle line:84%
of our emotional
processing occurs,

00:04:12.019 --> 00:04:15.155 align:middle line:84%
and then terminates all the
way here in the neocortex;

00:04:15.155 --> 00:04:17.725 align:middle line:84%
higher perceptual
centers of our brain.

00:04:17.725 --> 00:04:20.994 align:middle line:84%
And, when researchers map
out the neurological traffic

00:04:20.994 --> 00:04:24.164 align:middle line:84%
in our bodies, they see that
the heart is actually sending a

00:04:24.164 --> 00:04:25.399 align:middle line:90%
whole lot of more information

00:04:25.399 --> 00:04:27.201 align:middle line:84%
than it ever received
from the brain.

00:04:27.201 --> 00:04:29.670 align:middle line:84%
So, it's a neurological
communication studies

00:04:29.670 --> 00:04:32.339 align:middle line:84%
through a field called
neurocardiology.

00:04:32.339 --> 00:04:33.674 align:middle line:84%
The second thing
they discovered is

00:04:33.674 --> 00:04:36.210 align:middle line:84%
that we have what's called
the blood pressure wave.

00:04:36.210 --> 00:04:38.479 align:middle line:84%
It means that when the heart
squeezes and pushes blood,

00:04:38.479 --> 00:04:41.081 align:middle line:84%
it's actually a wave of energy
that's pushing that blood

00:04:41.081 --> 00:04:42.315 align:middle line:84%
through the veins
and the arteries,

00:04:42.315 --> 00:04:44.585 align:middle line:84%
and it goes through
obviously the whole body.

00:04:44.585 --> 00:04:47.488 align:middle line:84%
Blood pressure waves, it
turns out, influence all kinds

00:04:47.488 --> 00:04:50.690 align:middle line:84%
of biological function,
including the brain.

00:04:50.690 --> 00:04:53.827 align:middle line:84%
The electrical activity in our
brain is actually synchronized

00:04:53.827 --> 00:04:56.263 align:middle line:84%
to changes occurring in
this blood pressure wave.

00:04:56.263 --> 00:04:59.800 align:middle line:84%
And, that's called a biophysical
form of communication.

00:04:59.800 --> 00:05:01.769 align:middle line:90%
The third way is biochemical.

00:05:01.769 --> 00:05:04.238 align:middle line:84%
This is another one of those
who knew kind of things.

00:05:04.238 --> 00:05:07.040 align:middle line:84%
In 1983, the heart was
actually reclassified

00:05:07.040 --> 00:05:08.842 align:middle line:90%
as part of hormonal system.

00:05:08.842 --> 00:05:11.779 align:middle line:84%
The reason was is they
discovered it produces several

00:05:11.779 --> 00:05:13.514 align:middle line:90%
very, very important hormones.

00:05:13.514 --> 00:05:16.917 align:middle line:84%
One of those, for example,
is called atriopeptide.

00:05:16.917 --> 00:05:19.086 align:middle line:84%
Atriopeptide has
an interesting job.

00:05:19.086 --> 00:05:21.455 align:middle line:84%
It reduces or mediates
the release

00:05:21.455 --> 00:05:23.791 align:middle line:90%
of the stress hormone, cortisol.

00:05:23.791 --> 00:05:26.960 align:middle line:84%
It produces another hormone,
which many of listeners

00:05:26.960 --> 00:05:30.397 align:middle line:84%
and viewers today have probably
heard of called oxytocin,

00:05:30.397 --> 00:05:32.966 align:middle line:84%
which has been generically
called the love hormone.

00:05:32.966 --> 00:05:34.334 align:middle line:90%
Researches now are seeing

00:05:34.334 --> 00:05:37.404 align:middle line:84%
that the heart is probably the
biggest producer of oxytocin

00:05:37.404 --> 00:05:42.009 align:middle line:84%
in our body, and that's a
biochemical communication.

00:05:42.009 --> 00:05:43.544 align:middle line:84%
So, these first three
ways are interesting,

00:05:43.544 --> 00:05:45.345 align:middle line:84%
and they're well-documented,
well-studied,

00:05:45.345 --> 00:05:48.315 align:middle line:84%
and I call them hardwired
biological

00:05:48.315 --> 00:05:50.651 align:middle line:90%
communication pathways.

00:05:50.651 --> 00:05:52.152 align:middle line:84%
The fourth way is where
it gets really cool

00:05:52.152 --> 00:05:53.387 align:middle line:90%
and more interesting to me.

00:05:53.387 --> 00:05:55.522 align:middle line:90%
It's the energetic heart.

00:05:55.522 --> 00:05:58.025 align:middle line:84%
You see, our heart is
actually an electrical organ.

00:05:58.025 --> 00:06:00.494 align:middle line:84%
If you or I go to the doctor,
the doctor says I'm going

00:06:00.494 --> 00:06:03.130 align:middle line:84%
to do your EKG now
or ECG they call it.

00:06:03.130 --> 00:06:04.565 align:middle line:84%
They put electrodes
around our chest,

00:06:04.565 --> 00:06:06.467 align:middle line:84%
and they get an electrical
signal

00:06:06.467 --> 00:06:09.036 align:middle line:84%
from the electricity being
produced by the heart,

00:06:09.036 --> 00:06:11.905 align:middle line:84%
and they determine something
about our physical health.

00:06:11.905 --> 00:06:13.774 align:middle line:84%
The heart is by far
the strongest source

00:06:13.774 --> 00:06:18.612 align:middle line:84%
of bioelectricity that we
have, 40-60 times more powerful

00:06:18.612 --> 00:06:21.915 align:middle line:84%
than the second most powerful
source, which is the brain.

00:06:21.915 --> 00:06:24.051 align:middle line:84%
So, this electrical energy
produced by the heart goes

00:06:24.051 --> 00:06:25.452 align:middle line:84%
to every single cell
in our body.

00:06:25.452 --> 00:06:28.522 align:middle line:84%
Now, here's where
it becomes more fun.

00:06:28.522 --> 00:06:32.059 align:middle line:84%
That signal is strong enough, it
creates an electromagnetic field

00:06:32.059 --> 00:06:34.962 align:middle line:84%
that goes out about
3-4 feet from the body,

00:06:34.962 --> 00:06:37.097 align:middle line:90%
surrounds us in 360 degrees.

00:06:37.097 --> 00:06:38.966 align:middle line:84%
Right now, you and
I are interfacing

00:06:38.966 --> 00:06:40.601 align:middle line:90%
at an electromagnetic level

00:06:40.601 --> 00:06:43.337 align:middle line:84%
from the electromagnetic
fields produced by our heart,

00:06:43.337 --> 00:06:46.907 align:middle line:84%
so it's radiates beyond
the skin out into space.

00:06:46.907 --> 00:06:49.776 align:middle line:84%
Now, that field changes
all the time.

00:06:49.776 --> 00:06:52.346 align:middle line:84%
The electrical energy in
the field will change.

00:06:52.346 --> 00:06:53.580 align:middle line:84%
And, you know what's
changing it?

00:06:53.580 --> 00:06:54.848 align:middle line:90%
Our emotions.

00:06:54.848 --> 00:06:57.618 align:middle line:84%
And what we're feeling
emotionally is determining what

00:06:57.618 --> 00:06:59.553 align:middle line:90%
frequencies are in that field.

00:06:59.553 --> 00:07:02.556 align:middle line:84%
If we're feeling frustrated
or angry, resentful,

00:07:02.556 --> 00:07:03.757 align:middle line:90%
those kind of feelings,

00:07:03.757 --> 00:07:06.026 align:middle line:84%
it produces what's called
an incoherent spectra,

00:07:06.026 --> 00:07:07.961 align:middle line:90%
chaotic field.

00:07:07.961 --> 00:07:13.367 align:middle line:84%
If we're feeling love, care,
compassion, appreciation,

00:07:13.367 --> 00:07:16.670 align:middle line:84%
those heart qualities that we've
all heard about our whole life,

00:07:16.670 --> 00:07:19.873 align:middle line:84%
the field becomes more
coherent and very ordered.

00:07:19.873 --> 00:07:21.008 align:middle line:90%
So, literally,

00:07:21.008 --> 00:07:23.043 align:middle line:84%
we are broadcasting this
information all the time

00:07:23.043 --> 00:07:26.813 align:middle line:84%
from our heart to every cell
in our body out into space,

00:07:26.813 --> 00:07:29.516 align:middle line:84%
and we're interfacing and
interacting with each other.

00:07:29.516 --> 00:07:30.517 align:middle line:90%
Now, this.

00:07:30.517 --> 00:07:31.919 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: So, that means

00:07:31.919 --> 00:07:35.622 align:middle line:84%
that information is constantly
being given from heart to heart.

00:07:35.622 --> 00:07:38.492 align:middle line:84%
Like right now, beyond the
words, there's something else

00:07:38.492 --> 00:07:39.960 align:middle line:84%
that is happening
here between us.

00:07:39.960 --> 00:07:41.795 align:middle line:90%
>> Martin: Absolutely there is.

