what I'm saying,

00:24:12.418 --> 00:24:14.987 align:middle line:84%
you begin to disassociate from
it some, and you begin to put

00:24:14.987 --> 00:24:17.557 align:middle line:84%
out more; you find a
place, and you begin to sort

00:24:17.557 --> 00:24:21.127 align:middle line:84%
of cultivate yourself back to
that place that feels normal

00:24:21.127 --> 00:24:22.461 align:middle line:90%
to you or best to you.

00:24:22.461 --> 00:24:24.997 align:middle line:84%
In the beginning it's hard
for people, because they live

00:24:24.997 --> 00:24:28.134 align:middle line:84%
so much from here, and they live
from the neck up, and the roar

00:24:28.134 --> 00:24:31.037 align:middle line:84%
of ambition and survival's
driving everything they do.

00:24:31.037 --> 00:24:33.172 align:middle line:84%
And so, when they begin to
learn HeartMath techniques,

00:24:33.172 --> 00:24:35.575 align:middle line:90%
it's like, it feels awkward.

00:24:35.575 --> 00:24:36.943 align:middle line:84%
With just a little
bit of practice

00:24:36.943 --> 00:24:40.213 align:middle line:84%
as you learn these
things, it reverses.

00:24:40.213 --> 00:24:44.250 align:middle line:84%
It feels awkward not to be here,
not to be connected to that.

00:24:44.250 --> 00:24:46.185 align:middle line:90%
That feels strange.

00:24:46.185 --> 00:24:48.154 align:middle line:90%
That feels out of place.

00:24:48.154 --> 00:24:49.388 align:middle line:90%
And, so for me, it's easy.

00:24:49.388 --> 00:24:53.459 align:middle line:84%
The road home is a shorter
road than it used to be.

00:24:53.459 --> 00:24:55.461 align:middle line:90%
I mean the road back to here.

00:24:55.461 --> 00:24:59.498 align:middle line:84%
I never measured my personal
growth around how many,

00:24:59.498 --> 00:25:01.567 align:middle line:84%
you know, really got
right all the time.

00:25:01.567 --> 00:25:03.703 align:middle line:84%
I measured it, and still
continue to measure it

00:25:03.703 --> 00:25:08.074 align:middle line:84%
by how fast I return to being
the Howard Martin I want to be

00:25:08.074 --> 00:25:10.409 align:middle line:90%
when I find out that I'm not.

00:25:10.409 --> 00:25:12.511 align:middle line:84%
It's the distance;
it's the time it takes.

00:25:12.511 --> 00:25:16.082 align:middle line:84%
So, some things that may
have upset me for a week,

00:25:16.082 --> 00:25:19.518 align:middle line:84%
