00:34:41.747 --> 00:34:42.914 align:middle line:90%
>> Lilou: Yep.

00:34:42.914 --> 00:34:43.849 align:middle line:84%
>> Martin: The earth
produces energetic fields.

00:34:43.849 --> 00:34:46.385 align:middle line:90%
Think of them as part of nature.

00:34:46.385 --> 00:34:48.653 align:middle line:84%
The part of the earth
as a living system.

00:34:48.653 --> 00:34:50.222 align:middle line:90%
There are two primary ones.

00:34:50.222 --> 00:34:52.557 align:middle line:84%
One is called the
geomagnetic field.

00:34:52.557 --> 00:34:53.758 align:middle line:90%
Most people know what that is.

00:34:53.758 --> 00:34:55.593 align:middle line:90%
It's what a compass picks up.

00:34:55.593 --> 00:34:59.031 align:middle line:84%
It's the field created by
the spinning by the iron core

00:34:59.031 --> 00:35:00.299 align:middle line:90%
at the center of the earth.

00:35:00.299 --> 00:35:03.268 align:middle line:84%
It creates an electromagnetic
field around the planet.

00:35:03.268 --> 00:35:05.804 align:middle line:84%
The other one is called the
ionosphere, and it's a field

00:35:05.804 --> 00:35:08.974 align:middle line:84%
that operates just
above the atmosphere.

00:35:08.974 --> 00:35:11.310 align:middle line:84%
It goes about 120 some
miles up into space.

00:35:11.310 --> 00:35:13.378 align:middle line:84%
It's less dense than
the geomagnetic field,

00:35:13.378 --> 00:35:14.913 align:middle line:90%
and they work together.

00:35:14.913 --> 00:35:17.316 align:middle line:84%
And what they do fundamentally
is they provide a protective

00:35:17.316 --> 00:35:18.851 align:middle line:90%
layer around the planet.

00:35:18.851 --> 00:35:20.752 align:middle line:84%
It protects us from
all the space stuff.

00:35:20.752 --> 00:35:24.223 align:middle line:84%
You know, solar radiation,
cosmic rays, all those things,

00:35:24.223 --> 00:35:26.758 align:middle line:84%
and without those fields,
we can't have life.

00:35:26.758 --> 00:35:28.060 align:middle line:84%
We can't have these
pretty flowers.

00:35:28.060 --> 00:35:28.860 align:middle line:90%
We can't have grass.

00:35:28.860 --> 00:35:30.095 align:middle line:90%
We can't have you and me.

00:35:30.095 --> 00:35:32.531 align:middle line:84%
You know, that would all
go away without the fields.

00:35:32.531 --> 00:35:35.334 align:middle line:84%
So, they literally
are part of the earth.

00:35:35.334 --> 00:35:37.402 align:middle line:84%
Now, those fields
are always changing,

00:35:37.402 --> 00:35:40.038 align:middle line:84%
and they're constantly
in fluctuation.

00:35:40.038 --> 00:35:43.909 align:middle line:84%
And research going on for a
long time has definitively shown

00:35:43.909 --> 00:35:48.580 align:middle line:84%
that changes in these fields
are creating changes in us,

00:35:48.580 --> 00:35:51.883 align:middle line:84%
